  "notes": "Primary data taken verbatim from the RFEG club page (12 rated recorridos, per-hole Hoyo/Hdcp/Par/Metros tables with Vc/Vs). All four main tee sets (Blancas, Amarillas, Azules, Rojas) share the same par and stroke-index allocation; each is WHS-rated for both men and women, so 8 tee entries are emitted with identical distances per color. Internal consistency verified: pars sum 36+36=72, SI is a permutation of 1-18, and each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to its RFEG total (6229/5903/5482/5132 m). RFEG also lists three special recorridos excluded here: 'Family Game - VERDES' (a par-58, 2604 m short configuration, Vc 58.6/Vs 82 F and 56.34/73 M) and 'Seniors FGCV' setups (Amarillas M 5749 m Vc 70.8/Vs 125; Rojas F 5133 m Vc 73.2/Vs 127) — these are non-standard competition configurations, not regular tee sets. Minor discrepancies in secondary sources: mScorecard (values labeled 'yards' but clearly meters) matches RFEG per hole except hole 7 (328 vs 322) and hole 17 (390 vs 380) on Blancas, total 6245 vs 6229 (likely pre-re-rating figures; club website also historically quoted 6245 m); GolfingHoliday (yards) agrees on all pars and 16/18 stroke indexes, swapping SI 10/14 between holes 4 and 9 relative to RFEG. RFEG figures were preferred throughout."
